FBIS4-50197 "drchi095_p_94008" FBIS-CHI-94-095 Daily Report 11 May 1994 Central-South Region Hubei Economic Delegation Signs Agreement in France Hubei Economic Delegation Signs Agreement in France HK1605060094 Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network in Mandarin 1000 GMT 11 May 94 HK1605060094 Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network Mandarin BFN [Text] On the invitation of (Oulette), speaker of the Aquitaine Regional Assembly in France, the Hubei provincial economic delegation led by Guan Guangfu held negotiations on economic and technological issues with approximately 40 persons in charge of the various departments of the region on the evening of 8 May. They reached a consensus on six areas, including economics, trade, science and technology, and talent exchanges. Both sides held a solemn ceremony late at night on 9 May to commemorate the signing of the letter of intention on establishing economic and technological cooperation ties. The Aquitaine region is the world's largest wine and brandy production base. Not only is the region developed in agriculture, forestry, and animal husbandry, but it also a production base for high technology products, such as aircraft, electronic, and medical equipment. The region attached great importance to the Hubei economic delegation's current visit and held a grand welcome banquet in honor of the delegation in the small hours of the morning. In a speech expressing his gratitude, Guan Guangfu said: The relations between Hubei and the Aquitaine region should be like the region's Garonne River and Hubei's Chang Jiang, both of which flow endlessly. As one of China's new investment hot spots, Hubei Province is pursuing the magnificent goal it charted. It is both a construction site and a vast consumption market. We can make up for each other's deficiencies by developing strong points and striving for common development in many areas. Chinese Ambassador to France Cai Fangbo, his wife, and Chen Jinren, chief representative to France of the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade, attended the negotiations and signing ceremony.
